A molded TPU heel counter is included for stability while underfoot a React midsole provides cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Vaporwaffle sacai Sesame Blue Void
description: Made in collaboration with Chitose Abe's Tokyo fashion label the sacai x VaporWaffle 'Sesame Blue Void' emerges with retro and modern inspiration. Drawing from the 1983 Pegasus and the VaporFly the shoe's hybrid construction is built with textile on the upper overlaid by leather and suede and finished in neutral tones. Blue Void marks one of the Swooshes and the heel patch while two tongues add to the double aesthetic. Underfoot a layered foam midsole provides cushioning split at the heel giving way to a waffle rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Vaporwaffle sacai Dark Iris
description: Nike tapped Chitose Abe's fashion label on the Sacai x VaporWaffle 'Dark Iris.' The shoe's retro-inspired construction combines elements of the Pegaus 83 and Vaporfly built with nylon suede and leather and finished in Dark Iris and Campfire Orange. Dual Swoosh branding marks the side wall with double laces and tongues adding to the aesthetic while the heel patch includes co-branding. Underfoot a partially split foam midsole provides cushioning and contrast giving way to a rubber waffle outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Vaporwaffle sacai Villain Red Neptune Green
description: The Sacai x VaporWaffle SP 'String Villain Red' released as part of a collaboration with the progressive fashion label. Drawing from a 2019 LDV Waffle from the two brands the shoe's upper is built with mesh overlaid by Villian Red and Neptune Green suede. The Swoosh tongue and laces all sport a double construction with a similiar design on the stacked midsole which includes a split heel.

shoeName: Nike Vaporwaffle sacai Sport Fuchsia Game Royal
description: The Sacai x VaporWaffle 'Sail' features a stacked construction. A collaboration between Nike and Sacai the shoe draws from their 2019 LDV Waffle release. As a result the shoe includes double tongues Swooshes and tongue tags. Co-branding marks the heel patch while underfoot the stacked midsole includes a split construction at the heel. A waffle outsole is included for traction.

shoeName: Nike React Phantom Run Flyknit 2 Flash Crimson Baltic Blue
description: The React Phantom Run Flyknit 2 'Crater' emerges with a neutral look highlighted by vibrant accents. The shoe's Flyknit upper appears primarily in grey with vibrant Flywire cables worked into the midfoot. A TPU heel counter provides stability while the tongue and heel pull-loops provide easy on and off as well as further color. Underfoot a React foam midsole is included for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 04 Iron Grey (W)
description: A sustainable shoe with a bold design the Wmns Space Hippie 04 'Iron Grey' features a neutral colorway. Built with deconstructed Flyknit the shoe's upper sports a heathered grey finish incorporating yarns made with post-industrial and post-consumer waste. A heel pull-loop is included for easy on and off while underfoot a speckled Crater Foam midsole provides cushioning. A modified waffle rubber outsole is included for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Black White
description: The Air Zoom Pegasus 37 'Black White' emerges with a classic two-tone look. The shoe's upper is built with textile finished in black and contrasted by white on the Swoosh branding. Underfoot the midsole provides contrast built with React foam and housing Zoom Air in the forefoot to provide cushioning. The outsole includes waffle pistons for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Carnivore Comme des Garcons Homme Plus Black
description: Bringing back the 1993 cross-trainer the Comme des Garçons Homme Plus x Air Carnivore 'Black' debuted at Comme des Garçons' Spring/Summer 2021 runway show in Tokyo. Appearing in all black the shoe's upper is built with a mesh base overlaid by tonal nubuck at the toe and heel with a high-cut neoprene collar supporting the design. A branded midfoot strap secures the fit and adds 3M reflective detailing while the heel contrasts the look with 'Comme des Garçons Homme Plus' in white.

shoeName: Nike Vaporwaffle sacai Black White
description: The Sacai x VaporWaffle 'Black White' released as part of a collaboration with the Japanese fashion label. Drawing from a 2019 LDV Waffle collaboration the shoe's upper is built with a mix of mesh and suede finished in black and white. The tongues and Swooshes all feature a double construction while co-branding marks the heel. Underfoot the stacked exaggerated midsole adds to the doubled-up look giving way to a waffle outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 04 Sail Astronomy Blue
description: A sustainable shoe the Space Hippie 04 'Astronomy Blue' is built with Space Waste Yarn which includes 85% recycled polyester built with plastic bottles t-shirts and yarn scraps. Finished in tan and subtly accented by the Swoosh branding a heel pull-loop provides easy on and off. Underfoot the speckled Crater Foam midsole incorporates 12% Nike Grind rubber as well as standard foams.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 03 Grey Volt
description: The Space Hippie 03 'Grey Volt' released as part of a sustainable collection. The shoe's upper is built with Space Waste Yarn which incorporates recycled plastic water bottles and T-Shirts. The sock-like upper is highlighted by a midfoot overlay worked into a midfoot strap while underfoot the Crater Foam midsole is built in part with Nike Grind rubber. Recycled ZoomX foam provides further cushioning.

shoeName: Nike ISPA Overreact Sandal Black
description: The ISPA OverReact Sandal 'Thunder Grey' released as part of Nike's experimental line. The shoe's upper emerges with a deconstructed look supported by webbing straps and a drawcord lacing system. Finished in Thunder Grey Obsidian and black the design is cushioned underfoot by a stacked React midsole which includes a tread pattern on the side wall. That same pattern marks the outsole which incorporates added rubber at the toe and heel for traction.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 02 Grey Volt
description: Releasing as part of a sustainable collection the Space Hippie 02 'Grey Volt' emerges with a recycled construction. The shoe's laceless design is built with a mix of recycled plastic water bottles and T-shirts supported by an elastic cuff as well as tongue and heel pull-loops. Underfoot the Crater Foam midsole is built with the help of Nike Grind rubber with the insole incorporating ZoomX scraps for further cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Vaporwaffle sacai Tour Yellow Stadium Green
description: Nike teamed up with the Japanese fashion label to create the Sacai x VaporWaffle 'Tour Yellow.' A follow-up to a layered LDV Waffle collaboration in 2019 the shoe emerges with a double tongue Swoosh and laces. The heel patch sports co-branding while a heel pull-loop provides easy on and off. Underfoot a split construction marks the heel of the stacked midsole giving way to a rubber outsole with a waffle pattern for traction.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 04 Mystic Navy
description: The Space Hippie 04 'Mystic Navy' brings a subdued look to its sustainable construction. Part of the Space Hippie line the shoe's upper features Flyknit built with recycled yarns taken from post-industrial and post-consumer waste. Rope laces and heel pull-loop support the fit while underfoot the speckled Crater Foam midsole continues the thematic build incorporates Nike Grind rubber along with standard foams for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 04 Summit White Hyper Crimson (W)
description: Part of a five-shoe collection the Wmns Space Hippie 04 'This Is Trash - Crimson' emerges wtih a sustainable construction. Built with Space Waste Yarn the shoe's Flyknit upper is constructed from roughly 90% recycled polyester. Underfoot a Crater Foam midsole built with Nike Grind rubber and recycled foam materials provides cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 01 Grey Volt
description: Part of an exploratory footwear collection utilizing 'space junk'—scrap materials taken from Nike factory floors—the Space Hippie 01 'Grey Volt' emerges with a recycled construction. The shoe's upper is built with a mix of recycled plastic water bottles T-shirts and yarn scraps finished in grey and highlighted by the Swoosh branding. Underfoot a Crater Foam midsole incorproates 15% Nike Grind rubber with the ZoomX foam insole built with leftovers from the production of the Vaporfly 4%.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 03 Vast Grey Hyper Crimson
description: The Space Hippie 03 'This Is Trash' released as part of a sustainable collection inspired by the idea of life on Mars. Built with Space Waste Yarn constructed from about 90% recycled polyester the shoe's upper incorporates FlyEase and FastFit technologies. Underfoot the speckled Crater Foam midsole incorporates Nike Grind rubber and foam compounds to provide cushioning.

shoeName: Nike M2K Tekno White Metallic Silver Black (W)
description: Based on the Monarch series the Nike Women's M2K Tekno ESS revamps the unique '90s look with comtemporary detailing. Issued in September 2019 this women's iteration features textured metallic silver inserts peeking out through cutouts in the leather upper. Stitched emblems speak to the vintage aesthetic and a TPU heel clip adds a modern touch. An outsized foam midsole and contrast rubber outsole complete the look.

shoeName: Nike Zoom Double Stacked Barely Volt (W)
description: The Zoom Double Stacked 'Barely Volt' emerges with a vibrant monochromatic colorway to go with its bold performance construction. Drawing from the Air Zoom AlphaFly NEXT% the upper is built with mesh overlaid by leather at the heel and finished in Barely Volt. Underfoot the midsole sports a cored-out construction that incorporates double-stacked Zoom Air to provide lightweight cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Carnivore Comme des Garcons Homme Plus White
description: The Comme des Garçons Homme Plus x Air Carnivore 'White' debuted at Comme des Garçons' Spring/Summer 2021 runway show in Tokyo reviving the 1993 trainer. The shoe's upper is built with a mix of mesh and synthetic leather finished in white and secured by adjustable straps. A high-cut neoprene collar supports the fit while the heel adds 'Comme des Garçons Homme Plus' in contrasting black. Underfoot Air in the forefoot and heel of the phylon midsole provides cushioning.

shoeName: Nike ISPA Road Warrior Clear Jade
description: Drawing from the Zoom Alphafly Next% and Nike Shox prototypes the ISPA Road Warrior 'Clear Jade' emerges with a bold construction. The shoe's upper is built with paneled mesh with rubberized overlays worked into the strap system. A split-toe construction supports the fit while undefoot the floating midsole incorporates visible Zoom Air in the forefoot and midfoot for cushioning. A rubber outsole is included for traction.

shoeName: Nike Pegasus Trail 2 Barely Volt Poison Green
description: The Pegasus Trail 2 'Barely Volt' sports a vibrant upper and neutral tooling. The shoe's upper is built with mesh supported by a midfoot cage and a faux gaiter piece around the collar. Underfoot a speckled React midsole provides cushioning giving way to a prominent rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike ACG Air Zoom AO Laser Crimson
description: The ACG Zoom Air AO 'Black Laser Crimson' is an amphibious hiking shoe. The shoe's upper is built with mesh finished in black and supported by concealed toggle laces. The heel counter accents the look in Laser Crimson and provides stability while the Swoosh branding sports 3M reflective detailing. Underfoot the heel of the midsole includes Zoom Air for cushioning with the sole unit itself sporting drain ports.

shoeName: Nike Daybreak Teal Tint Midnight Navy
description: The Daybreak SP 'Teal Tint' brings an updated construction to the vintage runner. The shoe's upper features a Nexkin base a translucent textile sporting a screen-printed Swoosh on the side wall. The eyestay toe and heel include suede overlays while underfoot a white foam midsole gives way to a rubber waffle outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Daybreak Type Black Menta
description: Part of Nike's experimental N.354 line the Daybreak-Type 'Anthracite Menta' features a prototype-inspired design drawn from the brand's archives. Featuring a 70s-style look the shoe's upper is built with semitranslucent mesh and suede overlays finished in black and highlighted by Menta on the Swoosh zigzag stitching and deconstructed heel patch. Underfoot a rubber waffle outsole offers traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Pale Ivory (W)
description: A pastel look the Wmns Air Zoom Pegasus 37 'Pale Ivory' released in April 2020. Built with textile the upper sports a color-blocked design with mismatched Swoosh branding adding further color. Semitransparent paneling provides breathability while internal bands are worked into the lacing system. Underfoot a React foam midsole works with Zoom Air in the forefoot to provide cushioning.

shoeName: Nike ACG Nasu Gore-tex Khaki
description: Part of Nike's All Conditions Gear line the ACG Air Nasu Gore-Tex 'Khaki Golden Beige' features inspiration from Japan's Mount Nasu. The shoe's neutral textile upper is bolstered by no-sew overlays with the design lines drawn from the Air Wallowa Air Humara and Air Terra Grand. The laces eyelets and heel branding all sport reflective detailing while Gore-Tex is included to waterproof the design. A lugged rubber outsole offers traction.

shoeName: Nike React Infinity Run Flyknit Blue Ribbon Sports
description: The React Infinity Run Flyknit 'Blue Ribbon Sports' pays tribute to Nike's origins as Blue Ribbon Sports. As a result the shoe's multilayer Flyknit upper sports a direct callout on the heel. A two-tone heel counter provides stability while underfoot the React foam midsole sports a higher stack height and wider shape for further support.

shoeName: Nike Pegasus Trail 2 Pure Platinum Fossil Laser Orange (W)
description: The Wmns Pegasus Trail 2 'Limelight Laser Orange' emerges with a pastel look. Built with Pure Platinum textile tan mesh overlays the fit with Laser Orange accenting the Swoosh branding. Underfoot a React midsole provides cushioning giving way to a rubber outsole with a shockwave-style traction pattern.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 White Black
description: The Air Zoom Pegasus 37 'Pure Platinum' features a classic colorway on its performance build. The shoe's upper is built with textile finished in white and supported by semitranslucent paneling for breathability. Internal bands are worked into the lacing system while the collar is designed to taper away from the Achilles. Underfoot the React foam midsole includes Zoom Air in the forefoot to provide cushioning.

shoeName: Nike React Vision Barely Volt Laser Crimson
description: The React Vision 'Barely Volt Pink' brings a vibrant look to its bold construction. Built with a mesh base the look is highlighted by hits of red and purple. Barley Volt emerges on the eyestay while an external heel counter is included for stability. Underfoot a white React midsole provides cushioning giving way to traction pods that climb up the forefoot and heel.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 04 White Multi (W)
description: Constructed with 25% recycled content by weight the Wmns Space Hippie 04 'Photon Dust' is a lifestyle shoe with vibrant accents. The shoe's Flyknit upper incorporates lightweight yarns made from post-industrial waste highlighted by a multicolor Swoosh stitched into the side wall. More multicolor accents mark the large heel pull-loop which provides easy on and off while underfoot a speckled Crater Foam midsole provides cushioning. A waffle rubber outsole is included for traction.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 04 Iron Grey
description: The Space Hippie 04 'Iron Grey' features a largely neutral look on its sustainable construction. The shoe's upper is built with Space Waste Yarn incorporating 85% recycled polyester finished in a heathered grey fashion. A heel pull-loop provides easy on and off while underfoot the Crater Foam midsole is built with a mix of Nike Grind and standard foams. Multicolor speckling on the tooling brings color to the look.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 01 Black Wheat
description: Part of Nike's sustainable footwear collection the Space Hippie 01 'Black Wheat' is a lightweight track-inspired shoe. The shoe's upper is built with Space Waste Yarn that incorporates about 85% recycled polyester with a unique lacing system and dual pull-loops supporting the fit. Underfoot a speckled Crater Foam midsole built in part with Nike Grind rubber gives way to prominent outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 04 Grey Volt (W)
description: The Wmns Space Hippie 04 'This Is Trash - Volt' released as part of a five-shoe pack inspired by the idea of sustainability and life on Mars. Bult with Space Waste Yarn created using about 90% recycled polyester the upper is highlighted by Volt on the Swoosh branding. Underfoot the tooling continues the sustainable build with a speckled Crater Foam midsole built with the help of Nike Grind rubber.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 04 Grey Volt
description: The Space Hippie 04 'Grey Volt' brings a sustainable construction to its bold design. Built with Space Waste Yarn the upper incorporates recycled plastic water bottles T-shirts and yarn scraps finished in grey and highlighted by the Swoosh branding. Underfoot the speckled Crater Foam midsole includes a mix of standard foams and Nike Grind rubber while the insole is built with recycled ZoomX foam to provide further cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 01 Vast Grey Hyper Crimson
description: The Space Hippie 01 'This Is Trash' released as part of a five-piece collection centered around sustainability. Built with Space Waste Yarn constructed from 90% recycled polyester the shoe's sock-like upper is highlighted by a uniquely stylized Swoosh. Underfoot the Crater Foam midsole is built with a mix of Nike Grind rubber and foam compounds while the sockliner incorporates ZoomX foam scraps.

shoeName: Nike Pegasus Trail 2 Black Dark Smoke Grey
description: The Pegasus Trail 2 'Dark Smoke Grey' brings a neutral look to its trail-ready construction. Built with a mesh base the upper is bolstered by a midfoot cage and a faux gaiter piece around the collar. A heel pull-loop provides easy on and off while underfoot the midsole incorporates React foam for cushioning. The rubber outsole includes durable nubs for traction.

shoeName: Nike Waffle Racer 2X Summit White (W)
description: Updating the classic runner the Wmns Waffle Racer 2X 'Summit White Volt' released in August 2020. Built with textile and overlaid by suede the upper is highlighted by a streak of Volt through the side wall. An embroidered Swoosh provides contrast in black matched by the heel patch and vamp. Underfoot the outsole sports an exaggerated waffle pattern that climbs up the forefoot.

shoeName: Nike React Vision Orange Volt (W)
description: The Wmns React Vision 'Pale Ivory' emergs with vibrant accents on its performance running construction. Built with mesh the neutral upper is highlighted by layered eyelets and a TPU heel counter with black on the tongue and heel pull-loops. Underfoot a React foam midsole provides cushioning with traction pods that climb up the toe and heel.

shoeName: Nike ISPA Overreact Shadowberry
description: The ISPA OverReact Flyknit 'Shadowberry' brings a largely neutral look to its bold construction. The shoe's Flyknit upper is built with excess yarns that create a unique pattern on each pair. A hook-and-loop closure secures the fit in place of traditional laces while underfoot the Nike React midsole is updated with a data-informed design. The outsole includes added rubber at the toe and heel for traction.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 02 Vast Grey Hyper Crimson
description: Part of a five-piece sustainable collection the Space Hippie 02 'This Is Trash' features a recycled construction. The upper incorporates Space Wase Yarn made of about 90% recycled polyester harvested from plastic bottles T-shirts and yarn scraps. Underfoot the Crater Foam midsole utilizes Nike Grind rubber as well as standard foam compounds with a recycled ZoomX foam sockliner adding further cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Waffle One Team Orange (W)
description: The Wmns Waffle One 'Fuchsia Gold' brings a vibrant look to its retro-modern construction. Built with transparent mesh the shoe's upper is overlaid by suede finished in a mix of Active Fuchsia and orange with leather on the Swoosh branding and a TPU heel counter offering stability. Underfoot a wedge foam midsole provides cushioning giving way to a waffle rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Daybreak Type Summit White Light Orewood Brown
description: A deconstructed take on the 1979 Daybreak the Daybreak-Type 'Light Orewood Brown' emerges with a neutral look. The shoe's upper is built with semitranslucent mesh in place of the usual nylon with the exposed-foam tongue and suede overlays staying intact. A stitched Swoosh outline emerges on the side wall while underfoot a foam midsole gives way to a prominent waffle outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike ACG Zoom Air AO Smoke Grey Amarillo
description: The ACG Zoom Air AO 'Grey Metallic Silver' brings vibrant accents to its amphibious hiking design. Built with mesh the upper appears in a greyscale fashion supported by a bootie construction and highlighted by hits of Amarillo throughout. Concealed toggle laces secure the fit while underfoot the midsole houses Zoom Air in the heel for cushioning. The outsole includes drain ports.

shoeName: Nike React Phantom Run Flyknit 2 Red Orbit
description: The React Phantom Run Flyknit 2 'Red Orbit' sports a vibrant contrasting look on its performant running construction. Built with Flyknit the shoe's upper is supported by Flywire cables at the midfoot eliminating the need for traditional laces. A heel counter is included for stability while tongue and heel pull-loops provide easy on and off. Underfoot a React foam midsole provides cushioning giving way to a rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike ISPA Overreact Sail Multi
description: Part of Nike's experimental line the ISPA OverReact Flyknit 'Light Bone' is built with excess yarns creating a one-of-a-kind look on each pair. The Flyknit upper is supported by hook-and-look straps in place of traditional laces while the design forgoes a sockliner to allow for direct contact with the React midsole underfoot. Rubber sections on the toe and heel of the outsole are included for added traction.

shoeName: Nike Dbreak-Type Dia de los Muertos
description: Part of a larger capsule collection the Daybreak Type 'Día de Muertos' celebrates the Day of the Dead. Inspired by the traditional altars associated with the holiday the shoe's retro-inspired construction emerges with a vibrant look highlighted by stylized detailing and a marigold flower graphic on the lateral heel. The leather heel patches include 'Para Mi' and 'Familia' to complete the design.

shoeName: Nike ISPA Overreact Sandal Wheat
description: The ISPA OverReact Sandal 'Club Gold' emerges with a neutral look on its bold outdoor construction. The shoe's layered build features black webbing straps worked into the drawcord lacing system which supports the fit. A large heel pull-loop provides easy on and off while underfoot the rugged tooling includes a React midsole for cushioning. The outsole incoporates rubber cladding under the toe and heel for traction.

shoeName: Nike Flow 2020 ISPA Spruce Aura
description: The ISPA Flow 2020 SE 'Spruce Aura' is a lightweight running shoe with vibrant accents. Built with textile the shoe's upper includes monomesh windows for breathability bolstered by an adaptive lacing system. A heel pull-loop provides easy on and off while underfoot the cored-out foam midsole provides cushioning. The toe and heel of the outsole incorporate translucent rubber for traction.

shoeName: Nike OverBreak SP College Grey
description: Drawing from the Daybreak and OverReact the OverBreak SP 'College Grey' emerges with a subdued look on its bold construction. The shoe's upper is built with textile and synthetic suede finished in neutral tones and secured by multicolor laces that highlight the look. An oversized Swoosh is worked into the side wall while underfoot a React midsole provides cushioning. The stylized outsole includes rubber in high-wear areas for traction.

shoeName: Nike React Vision White Particle Grey (W)
description: The React Vision 'White Iridescent' brings an almost-monochromatic look to its bold performance construction. Built with mesh the upper appears in white save for iridescent detailng on the eyestay. A Particle Grey Swoosh complements the side wall while an external heel counter is included for stability. The tongue sports D/MS/X branding while underfoot a React midsole provides cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Zoom Double Stacked Black (W)
description: The Wmns Zoom Double Stacked 'Volt Black' features a contrasting look on its modern performance construction. The shoe's semitranslucent mesh upper appears in black with tonal leather overlaying the heel. Tongue and heel pull-loops provide easy on and off while underfoot the midsole includes layered Zoom Air in the forefoot and heel finished in Volt to provide cushioning.

shoeName: Nike React Vision Washed Coral (W)
description: The Wmns React Vision 'Washed Coral' brings a vibrant look to its bold construction. The shoe's upper is built with perforated mesh accented by a layered eyestay and supported by a TPU heel counter that extends past the heel. Tongue and heel pull-loops provide easy on and off while underfoot the React foam midsole provides cushioning. Rubber pods on the outsole offer traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Spiridon Cage 2 White University Blue (W)
description: A women's shoe the Wmns Air Zoom Spiridon Cage 2 'White University Blue' sports a two-tone look. Built with a mesh base the upper is overlaid by leather with open sections around the collar for breathability. University Blue accents the Swoosh and tongue pull-loop matched underfoot by the cage around the Zoom Air unit which provides cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Black
description: The Air Zoom Pegasus 37 'Black Dark Grey' brings a blacked-out look to its performance running construction. Built with one-piece textile the upper includes mesh for breathability with a midfoot band supporting the fit. Underfoot the tonal React midsole includes a larger Zoom Air unit in the forefoot for cushioning giving way to a waffle rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Waffle Racer Crater Barely Volt (W)
description: The Wmns Waffle Racer Crater 'Barely Volt' emerges with a vibrant look on its sustainable construction. The shoe's upper features a Barely Volt base highlighted by the Swoosh branding and prominent stitching. Grey suede appears at the forefoot and heel while underfoot the Crater foam midsole incorporates recycled materials giving way to a prominent waffle rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike ISPA Road Warrior Sail
description: Inspired by numerous Nike shoes the ISPA Road Warrior 'Volt' emerges with a bold construction. Serving as a nod to the Air Zoom Alphafly Next% the floating open heel draws from early Nike Shox prototypes. The Air Zoom BB NXT influence emerges on the double-stacked Zoom Air pods underfoot. The upper itself includes a knit patch construction that works with a split toe for stability.

shoeName: Nike Flow 2020 ISPA Medium Olive
description: The ISPA Flow 2020 SE 'Medium Olive' features vibrant tooling on its lightweight construction. The shoe's upper is built with textile accented by a camo-style pattern throughout its construction. Monomesh windows are included for breathability while a unique lacing system supports the fit. Underfoot the foam midsole provides cushioning while highlighting the look giving way to a semitranslucent rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike React Vision Light Orewood Brown
description: The React Vision 'Light Orewood Brown' brings a largely neutral look to its bold construction. Built with seamless mesh the upper is highlighted by the layered eyestay while exposed stitching adds to the aesthetic. Tongue and heel pull-loops provide easy on and off with an external heel counter providing stability. Underfoot a React midsole is included for cushioning giving way to an outsole with traction pods.

shoeName: Nike Joyride Run Flyknit Pure Platinum
description: The Joyride Run Flyknit 'Black Iron Grey' brings a simple colorway to its modern performance construction. The shoe's knit upper is supported by an inner bootie construction with a one-piece foam collar for comfort. The tongue accents the look while underfoot the foam midsole incorporates a series of beads in strategically placed pockets to provide cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Tailwind 79 Worldwide White Volt Blue Fury
description: The Air Tailwind 79 'Worldwide Pack' brings vibrant branding to its classic construction. Built with nylon the shoe's neutral upper is overlaid by black suede with the mismatched Swooshes in Blue Fury and Volt. More Volt marks the heel patch and tongue tag while underfoot a foam midsole gives way to a waffle rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike ZoomX Vista Grind White Multi (W)
description: The Wmns ZoomX Vista Grind 'Green Strike Vivid Purple' brings a vibrant look to its bold construction. Featuring a recycled design the shoe's lifted midsole incorporates production scraps left over from ZoomX runners. Up top the shoe emerges with a transparent textile build bolstered by no-sew overlays and supported by an external heel counter that provides stability.

shoeName: Nike ACG Air Nasu Black Olive
description: The ACG Air Nasu 'Black Cargo Khaki' features a subdued look on its retro-inspired construction. The shoe's upper is built with black mesh bolstered by no-sew overlays and accented by reflective eyelets. A heel pull-loop provides easy on and off while underfoot the speckled midsole houses Air in the heel to provide cushioning. A lugged rubber outsole is included for traction.

shoeName: Nike Shox R4 Metallic Gold Black
description: The Shox R4 'Metallic Gold' emerges with a vibrant contrasting look. Built with a mix of perforated leather and synthetic the upper appears in a mix of black and metallic gold. Underfoot the heel of the midsole incorporates the silhouette's signature Shox columns working with phylon in the forefoot for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Spiridon Cage 2 Varsity Royal (2020)
description: Bringing back the 2003 runner the Zoom Spiridon Cage 2 'Varsity Royal' released in June 2020. The shoe's upper features a dual-layer mesh construction overlaid by synthetic leather and finished in a mix of Varsity Royal and metallic silver. Underfoot the foam midsole houses the classic caged Zoom Air unit in the heel.

shoeName: Nike ACG Nasu Gore-tex Black
description: Inspired by Japan's Mount Nasu the ACG Air Nasu Gore-Tex 'Black Dark Grey' emerges with a weatherized construction. The shoe's textile upper appears in black accented by reflective detailing on the laces eyelets and heel pull-loop. Gore-Tex adds a waterproof construction to the design while underfoot the midsole includes speckling throughout giving way to a lugged rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Max Zephyr Green Abyss
description: The Air Max Zephyr 'Green Abyss' brings a vibrant look to its progressive construction. The shoe's mesh upper appears in Green Abyss and Aquamarine overlaid by Grey Fog synthetic leather and sporting Air bubbles highlighted by orange Swoosh branding. The tongue also includes an Air bubble that doubles as the tongue tag while underfoot the 720 Max Air unit in the midsole provides cushioning giving way to a translucent rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Daybreak Topaz Gold Cedar
description: The Daybreak SP 'Topez Gold' emerges with a contrasting look. Updating the 1979 runner the shoe's upper is built with Nexkin overlaid by hairy suede and finished primarily in Topaz Gold. The Swoosh branding and heel patch contrast the look in Cedar while underfoot a white foam midsole gives way to a rubber outsole with prominent waffle pattern for traction.

shoeName: Nike Zoom Gravity Black Metallic Silver
description: The Zoom Gravity 'Black' brings a simple colorway to its running construction. Designed for shorter runs the shoe's upper is built with aerodynamic mesh finished primarily in black with silver around the Swoosh branding. An upturned collar is designed to reduce Achilles irritation while underfoot the dual-density foam midsole includes Zoom Air in the forefoot for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike React Infinity Run Flyknit Premium Pink Blast (W)
silhoutte: Nike React Infinity Run Flyknit Premium
Colorway: Violet Ash/Pink Blast/Atomic Pink/Dark Smoke Grey
description: The Wmns React Infinity Run Flyknit Premium 'Violet Ash' brings a vibrant look to its performance running construction. The shoe's one-piece Flyknit upper sports a neutral finish overlaid by a no-sew skin around the heel with geometric designs. Underfoot the React foam midsole sports an elevated stack height and further color giving way to a rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Spiridon Cage 2 size? Carnaby
description: Nike teamed up with the UK retailer to create the size? x Air Zoom Spiridon Cage 2 'Carnaby Street.' Inspired by the historic shopping district in London's West End the shoe's upper is built with mesh overlaid by suede and leather and finished in a vibrant mix of hues. The heel also sports 'Welcomes the World' while a caged Zoom Air unit in the heel provides cushioning.

shoeName: Nike ZoomX Vista Grind Pale Ivory Black (W)
description: A modern fusion the Nike Women's ZoomX Vista Grind takes its cues from the street and the runway. Unveiled in October 2019 this women's rendition showcases a Pale Ivory textile upper with glimmering Swooshes a molded heel clip and off-centered TPU eyestays. A vintage badge on the tongue imbues the look with old-school running flair. Riding above the translucent rubber outsole the elevated midsole encapsulates Zoom X foam for a responsive cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Betrue (2020)
description: Celebrating the LGBT community the Air Zoom Pegasus 37 'Be True' sports a vibrant colorway. The shoe's textile upper emerges with a black base highlighted by a gradient mix of rainbow hues throughout its construction including on the Swoosh. The tongue and heel both sport 'Be True' branding while the Air Zoom branding on the midsole includes a rainbow flag. The technology itself emerges inside the React foam midsole for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike ACG Moc 3.0 Tie-Dye
description: A vibrant look the ACG Moc 3.0 'Tie-Dye' released in May 2020. Built with quilted textile the upper sports a tie-dye pattern throughout its construction which includes a mesh window on the medial side for breathability. Tongue and heel pull-loops provide easy on and off while underfoot a speckled foam midsole provides cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Iron Grey
Colorway: Iron Grey/Particle Grey-Photon Dust-Light Smoke Grey
description: The Air Zoom Pegasus 37 'Particle Iron Grey' brings a greyscale colorway to its lightweight performance construction. Built with one-piece textile the upper includes translucent mesh paneling for breathability. Internal midfoot bands are integrated into the lacing system while underfoot a React foam midsole incorporates Zoom Air in the forefoot to provide cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Daybreak Type Burgundy Royal
description: A vintage runner the Daybreak Type 'Red Racer Blue' emerges with vibrant color-blocking. The shoe's upper is built with semitranslucent mesh finished in Team Red with Racer Blue on the tongue heel and suede forefoot. Teal marks the stitching Swoosh and inner lining while the heel and tongue tag include N.354 branding. Underfoot a black rubber waffle outsole provides traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Premium Barely Rose (W)
description: The Wmns Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Premium 'Barely Rose Spruce' sports vibrant accents on its modern performance construction. The shoe's mesh upper appears primarily in Barely Rose with orange and green highlighting the internal bands worked into the lacing system. The lateral side sports double Swoosh branding while underfoot the midsole houses Zoom Air for cushioning with Pink Blast further accenting the lateral side.

shoeName: Nike Joyride CC Anthracite Volt Black
description: The Joyride CC 'Black Volt' sports a simple colorway with vibrant accents. Built with stretchy textile the upper is overlaid by tonal synthetic leather. Volt brings color to the heel and tongue lining while underfoot the white midsole houses NRGY Beads in further Volt to provide cushioning. A rubber outsole is included for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Be True (2020) (W)
description: The Air Zoom Pegasus 37 'Be True' released as part of Nike's 2020 Pride collection. Built with a black textile base the upper is highlighted by a rainbow gradient throughout matched by the Swoosh branding. The tongue and heel sport 'Be True' as does the React foam midsole underfoot. Zoom Air in the forefoot provides further cushioning.

shoeName: Nike ACG Moc 3.0 Midnight Navy Sanded Purple
description: The ACG Moc 3.0 'Midnight Navy' was designed in Oregon. The shoe's slip-on construction sports a quilted textile upper in Midnight Navy with mesh on the medial side for breathability. Tongue and heel pull-loops provide easy on and off while underfoot a foam midsole provides cushioning. The outsole incorporates black rubber at the toe and heel.

shoeName: Nike Venture Runner N7 (2020)
description: Part of Nike's summer 2020 collection the Venture Runner 'N7' celebrates Native American and Indigenous communities in North America. Drawing from medicinal plants the shoe features a floral print throughout its textile construction. Supported by suede overlays and a TPU heel counter the classic midsole houses the usual visible Air in the heel for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Huarache Run FB Black Poison Green
description: The Air Huarache ‘Poison Green’ highlights the shoe’s molded heel cage by coating the structural component in a vibrant green hue. It stands out against a monochromatic black backdrop which includes the shoe’s mesh toe neoprene interior bootie synthetic suede overlays and sculpted foam midsole. Underfoot the rubber outsole is finished in unexpected light blue.

shoeName: Nike ZoomX Vista Grind Black Pink (W)
description: Innovation comes to the forefront in Nike Women's ZoomX Vista Grind which showcases revoltionary design grounded in running-shoe DNA. Released in October 2019 this women's version displays an Off Noir textile upper accented with delineated Swooshes a synthetic toe cap and vintage tongue emblem. Molded eyestays and a TPU heel clip boost the utility look. A Zoom X-cushioned heightened midsole and translucent rubber outsole fuse street style and fashion-forward vibes.

shoeName: Nike Air Skarn Black Habanero Red
description: Dropping in October 2019 the Nike ACG Air Skarn 'Habanero Red' offers a modern interpretation of the outdoor sneaker originally released in 1997. This lighter-weight version makes use of a black textile upper with contrast blue stitching and matching black overlays for added durability. The speckled foam midsole features encapsulated Nike Air cushioning and extra lateral support at the midfoot.

shoeName: Nike Joyride CC3 Setter White Monsoon Blue
description: The Joyride CC3 Setter 'Vast Grey' brings a largely neutral look to its performance construction. The shoe's upper is built with mesh finished in white and complemented by textured and semitranslucent overlays. Hits of red highlight the look while a padded collar and deconstructed tongue support the fit. Underfoot the midsole houses a series of beads for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Joyride Nova Black (GS)
description: The Joyride Nova GS 'Black' is a grade-school exclusive with a bold construction and a subdued colorway. The shoe's slip-on neoprene bootie upper appears in black supported by a padded collar midfoot strap and molded side panels contrasted by white hits on the branding. Mesh at the forefoot is included for breathability while underfoot a black Joyride midsole includes visible TPE beads in the heel for cushioning. A rubber outsole provides traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Footscape Woven Chukka Rainbow
description: The Air Footscape Woven Chukka PRM QS dresses the mid-top silhouette in an off-white suede upper dominated by woven detailing in rainbow hues. Details include offset lacing for an optimal fit and stretchy neoprene collar for easy on and off. A lightly speckled Free-inspired midsole features flex grooves to accommodate the natural motion of the foot.

shoeName: Nike Air Tailwind 79 Hydrogen Blue
description: The Air Tailwind 79 'Hydrogen Blue' brings a subdued colorway to its retro running construction. Built with mesh the upper appears in Game Royal overlaid by light blue suede and leather on the Swoosh and heel patch. Underfoot the midsole houses Air for cushioning giving way to a waffle traction pattern on the rubber outsole.

shoeName: Nike Air Max Zephyr Photon Dust (GS)
description: The Air Max Zephyr GS 'Photon Dust Pink' is a grade-school shoe with vibrant accents. Built with mesh the shoe's upper features a Photon Dust base highlighted by Hyper Pink no-sew overlays and Volt upper eyelets while inflated Air pods at the tongue and side wall support the fit. A heel pull-loop provides easy on and off while underfoot a 720 Max Air unit provides cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Zoom Fly 3 Photon Dust (W)
description: The Wmns Zoom Fly 3 'Photon Team Orange' is a long-distance shoe with a pastel look. Inspired by the Nike Vaporfly the shoe's upper is built with Vaporweave finished in a translucent fashion that showcases the internal arch band that's integrated into the lacing system. Underfoot the React foam midsole provides cushioning working with a carbon fiber plate for stability.

shoeName: Nike Cortez Basic Leather South Beach
description: The Nike Cortez Basic Leather ‘South Beach’ name stems from its distinctive color palette combining a Blue Gale leather upper with contrasting pops of Laser Fuchsia on the laces and midsole. Those vibrant hues are offset by basic black on the eyestay heel tab toe overlay and leather Swoosh. Underneath it all a rubber herringbone outsole delivers traction.

shoeName: Nike Vista Lite University Blue Ghost Green (W)
description: The Wmns Vista Lite 'Flower Prints' is a women's shoe with unique detailing. The shoe's upper is built with mesh finished in University Blue and accented by floral graphics. Zigzag stitching adds to the aesthetic while colorful pull-loops provide easy on and off. A Swoosh stands out on the side wall while underfoot a one-piece foam midsole includes an angular heel for a more natural stride.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Champagne (W)
description: The Wmns Air Zoom Pegasus 37 'Champagne' brings a neutral look to the modern performance runner. Built with lightweight textile and semitranslucent mesh paneling the upper appears entirely in Champagne and Barely Rose. Underfoot the React foam midsole works with a Zoom Air unit in the forefoot to provide cushioning.

shoeName: Nike React Miler Black Laser Crimson
description: The React Miler 'Laser Crimson' features a classic colorway with vibrant accents. The shoe's upper is built with mesh finished in black with tonal no-sew overlays. Reflective detailing accents the look as do the Laser Crimson hits throughout. A heel pull-loop provides easy on and off while underfoot a React foam midsole includes an angular heel for a more natural stride.

shoeName: Nike Air Huarache Run Print Aloha (W)
description: The Wmns Huarache Run Print 'Aloha' works an Aloha print subtly into its running design. The textured red leather and neoprene upper which also includes mesh at the toe sports a vibrant print underneath its overlays and heel counter. A Sail midsole houses Air cushioning while a black outsole provides traction.

shoeName: Nike Joyride Dual Run White Black Multi
description: The Joyride Dual Run 'A.I.R.' released as part of Nike's Aritist in Residence series. Featuring input from A. Savage the shoe's upper sports colorful overlays drawing from national flags and costumes. Built with perforated mesh the upper is supported underfooted by a foam midsole that houses NRGY beads for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Black Valerian Blue Ghost Green
description: The Air Zoom Pegasus 37 'Valerian Blue' brings a subtly colorful palette to its performance build. The shoe's upper is built with textile finished in black and Valerian Blue. A Ghost Green Swoosh accents the side wall while internal bands are worked into the lacing system. Underfoot the React midsole houses Zoom Air for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Joyride Dual Run White Black Laser Crimson (W)
description: The Wmns Joyride Dual Run 'White Pink Crimson' highlights its unique tooling with vibrant accents. Underfoot the heel and forefoot of the midsole sport translucent pockets that house tiny foam beads designed to conform over time and create a personalized fit. The upper instead appears with a more neutral base built with textile and sporting a heel pull-loop for easy on and off.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Wildhorse 6 Sequoia
description: The Zoom Wildhorse 6 'Olive' features a utilitarian colorway on its trail construction. Built with a mix of mesh and ripstop no-sew overlays are included for durability. The upper is supported by a sock-like collar with a heel pull-loop for easy on and off. Underfoot React foam provides cushioning in the midsole giving way to a lugged rubber outsole with an anti-clog coating.

shoeName: Nike Epic React Flyknit 2 Teal Tint (W)
description: The Wmns Epic React Flyknit 2 'Teal Tint' brings a vibrant one-tone look to its performance running construction. The shoe's Flyknit upper appears entirely in Teal Tint supported by a slip-on collar and a molded eyestay. An external heel counter is included for stability also being reduced for a lighter fit. Underfoot a React midsole completes the monochromatic design while providing cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Waffle Racer 2X Ghost Dark Beetroot (W)
description: Released in August 2020 the Wmns Waffle Racer 2X 'Ghost Light Bone' updates the classic runner. The shoe's semitranslucent ripstop upper emerges in various shades of light blue with the Swoosh outline contrasting the design. A French terry lining is included for comfort while underfoot the outsole sports large rubber lugs that climb up the forefoot for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Black White (W)
description: A classic two-tone look the Wmns Air Zoom Pegasus 37 'Black White' is a performance runner. Built with black textile the upper is supported by internal bands worked into the lacing system. A white Swoosh contrasts the side wall matched underfoot by the React foam midsole which also houses Zoom Air for cushioning. A black rubber outsole anchors the design.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Obsidian Mist
description: The Air Zoom Pegasus 37 'Obsidian Mist' features vibrant accents on its neutral base. The shoe's upper is built with textile finished in grey and highlighted by the internal bands and side wall Swoosh. A tapered collar is designed to reduce Achilles irritation while underfoot a React midsole provides cushioning working with a Zoom Air unit in the forefoot. A waffle rubber outsole is included for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Vomero 14 Grey Fog Volt
description: The Air Zoom Vomero 14 'Smoke Grey Volt' sports vibrant accents on its neutral base. The shoe's upper is built with mesh finished in grey and supported by integrated Flywire cables. Foam pods in the heel are included to secure the fit while underfoot the Nike React midsole incorporates a full-length Zoom Air unit for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike React Phantom Run Flyknit 2 Teal Tint (W)
description: The Wmns React Phantom Run Flyknit 2 'Teal Tint Aurora' brings a subdued look to its everyday running construction. The shoe's upper is built with Flyknit supported by Flywire cables around the midfoot. The slip-on design is bolstered by an external heel counter while underfoot a white React foam midsole provides cushioning. Tongue and heel pull-loops up top provide easy on and off.

shoeName: Nike Zoom Double Stacked Smoke Grey (W)
description: The Wmns Zoom Double Stacked 'Volt Black' features a contrasting look on its modern performance construction. The shoe's semitranslucent mesh upper appears in black with tonal leather overlaying the heel. Tongue and heel pull-loops provide easy on and off while underfoot the midsole includes layered Zoom Air in the forefoot and heel finished in Volt to provide cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Obsidian Mist (GS)
description: The Air Zoom Pegasus 37 GS 'Obsidian Mist' is a grade-school shoe. Built with mesh the shoe's neutral upper reveals Lotus Pink bands worked into the lacing system. Underfoot the bulky foam midsole includes Zoom Air in the forefoot for cushioning giving way to a rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Alphina 5000 White Multi-Color (W)
description: The Wmns Alphina 5000 '2000s' celebrates the start of the millenium with a colorful DIY-style design. Built with a mesh base the upper sports no-sew overlays in a series of vibrant hues. Visible Flywire cables support the fit while underfoot a dual-density sockliner works with a foam midsole for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 White Multi-Color Crimson
description: Inspired by 5K color runs the Air Zoom Pegasus 37 'Paint Splatter' features vibrant accents. The shoe's upper is built with textile finished in white and supported by integrated midfoot bands which highlight the design. More color is provided by the Swoosh and heel strip while mesh panels are included for breathability. Underfoot the React midsole includes forefoot Zoom Air for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 White Metallic Silver (W)
description: The Wmns Air Zoom Pegasus 37 'White Metallic Silver' emerges with a clean colorway on its modern performance construction. Built with textile the upper appears in white with a midfoot band and tapered collar supporting the fit. A metallic silver Swoosh accents the side wall while underfoot the React foam midsole includes forefoot Zoom Air for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike React Miler Ozone Blue
description: The React Miler 'Celestine Blue' is a long-distance runner with a neutral look. Built with mesh the upper appears in Ozone Blue Midnight Navy and Celestine Blue with reinforced eyestays supporting the fit. A wider forefoot shape bolsters the design while underfoot a contrasting React foam midsole provides cushioning. The outsole incorporates high-abrasion rubber in high-wear areas.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Fire Pink (GS)
description: The Air Zoom Pegasus 37 GS 'Fire Pink' emerges with a vibrant look on its grade-school construction. The shoe's mesh upper includes semitransparent paneling on the side wall with a white Swoosh on the quarter panel. Rather than Flywire cables the fit is supported by internal bands integrated into the lacing system. Underfoot a foam midsole incorporates Zoom Air for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Flex 2020 RN University Red
description: Featuring a vibrant look the Flex 2020 RN 'University Red' is a running shoe designed for shorter runs. Built with stretch mesh the shoe's upper sports a mix of University Red and black with internal straps worked into the lacing system for support. A deconstructed heel supports the fit while dual pull-loops provide easy on and off. Underfoot the contrasting dual-density foam midsole gives way to flex grooves on the outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Black Valerian Blue Ghost Green (GS)
description: The Air Zoom Pegasus 37 GS 'Valerian Blue' is a grade-school shoe with vibrant accents. Featuring semitransparent mesh the shoe's upper sports a black base complemented by Valerian Blue with Ghost Green highlighting the Swoosh branding. The contrasting midsole houses Zoom Air for cushioning giving way to an outsole with waffle-pistons for traction.

shoeName: Nike Joyride Nova Laser Fuchsia (GS)
description: The Joyride Nova GS 'Laser Fuchsia is a grade-school exclusive look. The shoe's upper sports a neoprene bootie construction with a padded collar for support. Finished in Laser Fuchsia and Orange Peel Light Blue Fury accents the branding with black contrast provided by the stitching and forefoot strap. A molded side panel provides stability with the Joyride midsole incorporating visible TPE beads in the heel for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Black Valerian Blue Ghost Green (W)
description: A women's runner the Wmns Air Zoom Pegasus 37 'Valerian Blue' is highlighted by the Ghost Green Swoosh on its side wall. Built with textile the upper appears in black and Valerian Blue working internal brands into its lacing system for support. Underfoot React foam works with Zoom Air to provide cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 37 Black Olive Crimson
description: The Air Zoom Pegasus 37 'Black Olive' brings a neutral look to its running construction. Built with breathable textile the upper appears in black complemented by olive. Internal bands support the fit while underfoot the contrasting white midsole incorporates a mix of React and Zoom Air to provide cushioning. The outsole adds color in red sporting waffle pistons for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Max Plus SE Air Max Running Club University Blue
description: Taken from the 'Air Max Running Club' collection inspired by the Athletics West running team founded in 1977 by Bill Bowerman Phil Knight and Geoff Hollister is the Nike Air Max Plus SE 'University Red Light Photo Blue.' Updated with an exposed-foam nylon tongue the retro runner features a blue textile upper with a crimson TPU cage and color-matched suede overlays. Woven tags on the lateral eyestay of each shoe show mismatched 'AMRC' and 'BVRTN OR' branding. On the bottom is a white polyurethane midsole with visible Max Air cushioning and a whale tail-inspired shank plate in a gradient blend of blue and yellow.

shoeName: Nike Waffle One Summit White
description: The Waffle One 'Summit White' brings a modern build to its heritage construction. Finished in a subdued mix of hues the shoe's upper is built with semitranslucent mesh overlaid by off-white suede and supported by a low-cut collar. Exposed zigzag stitching adds to the aesthetic while a TPU heel counter offers stability. Underfoot a stacked foam midsole provides cushioning giving way to a waffle rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike React Phantom Run Flyknit 2 White Black
description: The React Phantom Run Flyknit 2 'Oreo' gets its name from its classic mix of colors. The shoe's Flyknit upper appears in white contrasted by black on the supportive Flywire cables. An external heel counter is included for stability while tongue and heel pull-loops are included for easy on and off. Underfoot a React midsole provides cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Zoom Alpha Fly Next Nature Flat Pewter
silhoutte: Nike Zoom Alpha Fly Next Nature
description: Made with at least 50% recycled content by weight and adding pastel accents is the Nike Zoom Alphafly Next Nature 'Rawdacious.' The upper is made out of breathable textile rendered in Flat Pewter with soft pink detailing on the tongue and collar with layers of processed TPU that's formed with an innovative 3D printing technology dubbed Nike Flyprint. On the bottom is lightweight cushioning with a combination of a carbon fiber spring plate and ZoomX foam midsole with two visible Zoom Air units under the forefoot.

shoeName: Nike LD Waffle SF sacai Fragment Grey
description: Nike teamed up with Chitose Abe and Hiroshi Fujiwara to create the Fragment Design x sacai x LDV Waffle 'Light Smoke Grey.' Drawing from both the LDV and the Waffle Racer the shoe's upper is built with a mesh base overlaid by stacked suede on the forefoot eyestay and heel. White leather marks the Swooshes with further doubled-up touches on the laces and tongue. Co-branding emerges on the elongated foam midsole that provides cushioning underfoot giving way to a contrasting black waffle rubber outsole that's included for traction.

shoeName: Nike LD Waffle SF sacai Fragment Blue Void
description: Bringing together two renowned Japanese labels the Fragment Design x sacai x LDV Waffle 'Blackened Blue' is a collaborative look. Combining features of the Nike LDV and Waffle Racer the shoe's hybrid construction emerges in mesh and suede finished in navy and contrasted by white throughout including on the dual leather Swooshes. The heel patch adds Nike and sacai branding while the double tongues sport Nike and fragment branding. Underfoot more co-branding marks the elongated foam midsole with a waffle rubber outsole included for traction.

shoeName: Nike LD Waffle sacai Undercover Black Bright Citron
description: Blending the design visions of Chitose Abe and Jun Takahashi is the sacai x Undercover x Nike LDWaffle 'Bright Citron.' It features a black nylon upper with double-layered details of overlapping Swooshes in yellow leather and shaggy off-white suede and ivory-colored leather and dark grey suede forefoot and heel overlays. Nylon tongues are similarly doubled-up with the black tongue having a woven tag marked with dual Nike and Undercover branding. A Nike/sacai logo is on the leather heel tab and a stacked foam midsole with a yellow waffle-traction rubber outsole.

shoeName: Nike React Phantom Run Flyknit 2 White Pure Platinum (W)
description: The Wmns React Phantom Run Flyknit 2 'True White Silver' features an almost-monochromatic look on its everday running construction. Built with Flyknit the upper is supported by Flywire cables. The heel counter adds color in silver while tongue and heel pull-loops provides easy on and off. Underfoot a React foam midsole is included for cushioning.

shoeName: Nike LD Waffle sacai Black Nylon
description: Released in March 2020 the Sacai x LDWaffle 'Black Nylon' doubles up its construction. Combining elements from the LDV and Waffle Racer the shoe's black nylon upper is overlaid by double Swooshes tongues laces and overlays while underfoot the contrasting white midsole extends past the heel.

shoeName: Nike Air Tailwind 79 White Phantom Black
description: The Tailwind 79 'Phantom White' takes cues from the legacy of the 1970s runner aesthetic. The shoe boasts a Phantom White-based mesh upper with coordinated suede overlays on the toe box eyestay and heel. The offering also features a padded tongue for soft support black leather hits on the heel patch and Swoosh and a waffle-tread on the outsole for improved traction.

shoeName: Nike Epic Phantom React Flyknit White Pure Platinum (W)
description: The Wmns Epic Phantom React Flyknit 'Triple White' washes out its performance construction. The shoe's breathable Flyknit upper emerges with a flexible–yet supportive–fit due to its combination of yarns while a heel counter adds stability. The data-informed React foam midsole provides cushioning while maintaining the one-tone look with a pressure-mapped outsole pattern providing traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Alphafly Next% Barely Volt Orange
description: Updating the pinnacle running shoe with a new color scheme is the Nike Air Zoom Alphafly Next% 'Barely Volt.' The AtomKnit upper that's a breathable lightweight update of Nike Flyknit features a neon green hue throughout. Gradient pastels fade to white on the ZoomX foam midsole that includes a full-length carbon fiber plate and is fitted with two visible Zoom Air units under the forefoot. Durable rubber pods are included on the outsole that has a traction pattern based on data from hundreds of other runners.

shoeName: Nike LD Waffle sacai CLOT Kiss of Death 2 Cool Grey
description: Inspired by CLOT's Air Max 1 release from 2013 comes the triple-threat collaboration shoe that is the sacai x CLOT x Nike LDWaffle 'Kiss Of Death 2.' The sneaker showcases neutral grey tones throughout an upper crafted from semi-translucent mesh with fused synthetic overlays. Nike x sacai x CLOT branding is featured on the leather heel tab with woven Nike tags on the grey and green nylon tongues. It is built on a double-stacked foam midsole that's reinforced underfoot by a waffle-traction gum rubber outsole.

shoeName: Nike LD Waffle sacai CLOT Kiss of Death Net Orange Blaze
description: Nike brings you a triple collaboration in the sacai x Clot x Nike LDWaffle 'Net Orange Blaze'. Drawing from the CLOT x Nike Air Max 1 'Kiss of Death' it combines features from the LDV and Waffle Racer. With a tan semi-translucent textile upper paired with tonal suede overlays at the forefoot and heel. The signature double Swooshes from sacai are brick red and orange leather with a slight snakeskin exterior. Subtle lime green color slashes the double-stacked eyestay triple-branded heel tab and the dual woven tags on top of the tongue. Grip down the street with waffle-traction and a two-tone midsole with an elongated heel.

shoeName: Nike Air Presto What The
description: The Air Presto 'What The' brings the mashup treatment to the T-shirt for your feet. Drawing from various OG colorways of the runner the shoe's mismatched uppers include a 'Rogue Kielbasa' vamp on the left shoe joined by a 'Shady Milkman' fleece collar and 'Unholy Cumulus' lacing cage. The right shoe instead sports a 'Trouble at Home' lightning design on the vamp with the 'Brutal Honey' getting the nod via a yellow mesh lining while the 'Orange Monk' citrus midsole provides cushioning underfoot. Even the sockliners are mismatched with the left shoe sporting '20' and the right sporting T-shirt sizing.

shoeName: Nike Epic React Flyknit 2 Black Anthracite
description: Sporting subtle flair the Nike Epic React Flyknit 2 ‘Black Anthracite’ exhibits a covert color palette on a high-performing runner that values speed and flexible cushioning. The latter arrives via a soft React foam midsole clad in dark grey Anthracite. A ventilated Flyknit upper is equipped to hug the foot for optimal support and comfort.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Tempo Next% Flyknit White Hyper Violet Flash Crimson
silhoutte: Nike Air Zoom Tempo Next% Flyknit
description: The Air Zoom Tempo Next% Flyknit 'White Hyper Violet' features a vibrant look on its performance running construction designed with the help of world-class runners. The shoe's Flyknit upper appears in white secured by an asymmetrical lacing system and supported by ZoomX foam in the insole. Underfoot the React midsole incorporates visible Zoom Air in the forefoot for cushioning giving way to a black rubber outsole designed to support high-wear areas.

shoeName: Nike Epic React Moc Flyknit White Hydrogen Blue
description: The Epic Phantom React Flyknit 'Hydrogen Blue' emerges with a simple blue look. The shoe's flexible Flyknit upper is finished in Hydrogen Blue with the laceless construction supported by an external heel counter which adds color. Tongue and heel pull-loops provide easy on and off while a React foam midsole is included for cushioning. A pressure-mapped pattern on the outsole provides traction.

shoeName: Nike LD Waffle sacai Undercover Night Maroon Team Royal
description: Part of a triple collaboration is the sacai x Undercover x Nike LDWaffle 'Night Maroon Team Royal.' Taking inspiration from the LDV and Waffle Racer this hybrid silhouette features a burgundy nylon upper with superimposed Swooshes in blue leather and off-white suede and double-stacked overlays in black leather and shaggy grey suede. Each heel tab has dual Nike and sacai branding with all three company labels being called out on the extended heel piece that distinguishes the stacked foam midsole. It's built on a blue waffle-traction rubber outsole.

shoeName: Nike P-6000 White Gold Red (W)
description: The Wmns P-6000 CNPT 'Metallic Silver Red' borrows design elements from the Pegasus 25 and Pegasus 2006. The casual runner is built with a mix of suede and leather on the upper finished primarily in black white and metallic silver. University Red emerges on the patent leather Swoosh which is outlined by gold. Underfoot a Cushlon midsole provides cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Structure OG White Neo Teal
description: Releasing for the 30th anniversary of the silhouette the Air Structure Triax 91 OG 'Neo Teal' 2021 brings back the retro runner with this March 2021 drop. Built with mesh the shoe's upper sports a white base overlaid by grey and black synthetic suede and highlighted by hits of Neo Teal and Infrared. An angular TPU heel counter provides stability while underfoot visible Max Air in the heel provides cushioning. A waffle rubber outsole offers traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Huarache Stussy Desert Oak (2021)
description: Released in 2021 the Stussy x Air Huarache LE 'Desert Oak' 2021 brings back a collaboration from 2000 between Nike's Fraser Cooke and Stussy UK's Michael Koppleman released exclusively at Stussy's London chapter store. The shoe's upper is built with a mix of textile and nubuck finished in a neutral mix of hues and supported by the signature external heel counter. Underfoot Air in the midsole offers cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Presto Off-White Black (2018)
description: The second collaboration between Virgil Abloh and Nike on the Air Presto the OFF-WHITE x Air Presto 'Black' features the designer's signature deconstructed aesthetic. Released shortly after its predecessor's release as part of The Ten collection the shoe's black mesh upper is accented by a white Swoosh with prominent stitching. 'Air' branding appears on the heel with branding text on the medial quarter panel. Supported by a lacing cage a tonal Phylon midsole provides cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Huarache Triple Red
description: A monochromatic finish allows the details of the Nike Air Huarache 'Triple Red' to stand out. They include a revolutionary neoprene bootie designed to hug the foot along with an exoskeletal cage that added structure without unnecessary weight. The sneaker’s sculpted midsole complete with embossed rows of dots packs encapsulated Air for responsive cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Presto Off-White White (2018)
description: The OFF-WHITE x Air Presto 'White' released in August 2018 a week after an all-black iteration. The shoe's deconstruction build is highlighted by rough seams and an exposed-foam tongue while the mesh construction maintains the signature build of the Air Presto. Virgil Abloh's tongue-in-cheek branding includes 'Air' on the heel with a red zip-tie hang-tag adding more color to the look.

shoeName: Nike Pegasus Trail 3 Gore-Tex Black Dark Smoke Grey
description: Delivering a sleek colorway of a performance running shoe made for harsher weather is the Nike Pegasus Trail 3 GTX 'Triple Black.' The seamless upper is made from black textile with tonal Gore-Tex branding on the toe box nodding to the waterproof lining of the interior. The midfoot is supported by a dynamic-fit band while a pull tab at the heel allows easy on and off. On the bottom is a matching black Nike React midsole with a durable lugged rubber outsole.

shoeName: Nike Epic Phantom React Flyknit Black White
description: The Epic Phantom React Flyknit 'Black' puts a simple two-tone look on its performance running construction. The shoe's Flyknit upper is finished entirely in black supported by tongue and heel pull-loops and an external heel counter. Underfoot a white React midsole provides cushioning and contrast giving way to a pressure-mapped traction pattern on the outsole.

shoeName: Nike ZoomX Vaporfly Next% Valerian Blue
description: The ZoomX VaporFly NEXT% 'Valerian Blue' is a performance runner with a vibrant look. Built with the engineered woven mesh known as VaporWeave the upper appears in Valerian Blue accented by purple on the eyestay and Vapour Green on the Swoosh branding. Underfoot more Vapour Green emerges on the ZoomX midsole which incorporates a full-length carbon fiber plate. Flex grooves on the outsole provide traction.

shoeName: Nike LD Waffle sacai Undercover Midnight Spruce University Red
description: Incorporating some of the design from the vintage LDV and Waffle Racer '70s runners is the sacai x Undercover x Nike LDWaffle. It features a dark teal finish on the stitched nylon upper with a red leather and off-white suede double-Swoosh and layered overlays in black leather and grey suede. A hybrid Nike/sacai logo is stamped on the leather heel tab with the secondary tongue having a discrete Undercover branding on the woven tag. It's built on a stacked off-white foam midsole with an extended heel and scarlet waffle-traction rubber outsole.

shoeName: Nike Cortez Basic Black White
description: This Bill Bowerman pet project gets a luxe update in the Nike Cortez Basic Black White leather sneaker.The Nike Cortez Basic Black White is dressed in classic black and white and the ’72 icon stays true with a premium leather upper with matching leather overlays. The mostly black sneaker is highlighted by white branding on the tongue sidewall and heel counter. A signature white foam midsole with a contrasting streak in the middle sits atop a serrated rubber outsole for a timeless touch.The Nike Cortez Basic Black White was released in January 2016 and retailed for $75.

shoeName: Nike React Element 55 Black White
description: There aren't too many shoes that look more classic than the Nike React Element 55 Black White. This sneaker comes with a black upper white Nike "Swoosh" and a white midsole with black accents. These released in September 2018 and retailed for $130. Compliment your outfit with these and place a Bid on StockX.

shoeName: Nike Space Hippie 01 Obsidian
description: Featuring a contrasting two-tone look the Space Hippie 01 'Obsidian' is a sustainable shoe. The shoe's knit upper is built with a mix of recycled T-shirts fabric scraps and plastic water bottles. The Obsidian look is complemented by lighter blue on the Swoosh and eyestay with tongue and heel pull-loops offering easy on and off. Underfoot an off-white Crater Foam midsole provides cushioning aided by a sockliner built with ZoomX foam scraps.

shoeName: Nike Epic Phantom React Flyknit Black White (W)
description: The Wmns Epic Phantom React Flyknit 'Black' emerges with a blacked-out colorway. The performance runner features a laceless Flyknit upper in black with tongue and heel pull-loops for easy on and off. A tonal heel counter provides stability while a white React midsole provides cushioning and contrast. The outsole incorporates a pressure-mapped traction pattern.

shoeName: Nike Waffle One Black White
description: Featuring a classic two-tone look the Waffle One 'Black' adds to the Waffle line. Built with semitranslucent mesh the shoe's upper appears in black with leather on the tonal Swoosh and suede overlaying the forefoot and heel. A TPU heel counter is included for stability while underfoot a white foam midsole provides cushioning and contrast sporting a classic wedge shape. A waffle rubber outsole offers traction completing the look in black.

shoeName: Nike Shox Ride 2 SP Supreme Olive
description: The Supreme x Shox Ride 2 'Neutral Olive' is part of a four shoe pack that also includes matching Nike Running hats. The upper utilizes Neutral Olive ventilated mesh panels with overlays arriving in leather and nubuck. Lime Green accents the Swoosh as well as the Shox logo on the tongue area. A visible Nike Air unit in the forefoot complements the Shox columns in the heel where 'Supreme' wordmarks can be seen on each individual pillar.

shoeName: Nike Zoom Terra Kiger 5 OFF-WHITE Electric Green (W)
description: The OFF-WHITE x Wmns Air Zoom Terra Kiger 5 'Athlete in Progress - Electric Green' is the result of a collaboration between Virgil Abloh and Nike. A women's shoe the upper is built with nylon and brushed suede overlays finished in Electric Green and brown. A retro-style finish emerges on the tongue supported by an asymmetrical lacing system with blue laces. Underfoot a Zoom Air midsole gives way to a spiked rubber outsole.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Tempo Next% Flyknit Black White
silhoutte: Nike Air Zoom Tempo Next% Flyknit
description: The Air Zoom Tempo NEXT% Flyknit 'Black White Volt' is an everyday training shoe. The shoe's upper is built with Flyknit finished in black and supported by synthetic no-sew overlays. An asymmetrical lacing system bolsters the fit while underfoot the midsole combines React with ZoomX foam sporting visible Zoom Air in the forefoot for added cushioning. A full-length plate is included for stability.

shoeName: Nike Air Presto Off-White
description: Part of The Ten capsule from Virgil Abloh and Nike the OFF-WHITE x Air Presto 'The Ten' emerges with a deconstructed look. The shoe's breathable upper features prominent seams with an exposed tongue and a sitched-on Swoosh which emerges underneath the white lacing cage. The heel strap and medial side quarter panel sport prominent branding with a zip tie hang-tag adding a hit of red on the left shoe.

shoeName: Nike Air Max Bolt Triple Black
description: Featuring a blacked-out look the Air Max Bolt 'Triple Black' is a lifestyle running shoe. Built with mesh and synthetic overlays the shoe's upper appears entirely in black supported by a TPU heel counter for stability. A tongue pull-loop is included for easy on and off while underfoot the black foam midsole with visible Max Air offers cushioning and continues the monochromatic design. A modified waffle traction pattern on the rubber outsole provides traction.

shoeName: Nike Shox Ride 2 SP Supreme Black
description: Supreme brings back a mid-2000s Nike Running silhouette the Shox Ride 2 with updated branding elements. This 'Black' colorway features a blacked out look across the mesh and leather upper. Hits of 3M can be found throughout with a white Swoosh on the back heel and white Shox logo on the tongue. 'Supreme' wordmarks can be found on each of the four Shox pillars working together with a forefoot visible Air unit.

shoeName: Nike Cortez Basic Leather White Black (2017)
description: Bill Bowerman first designed the Nike Cortez in 1972. Since then the silhouette has been redesigned in countless colorways but nothing beats a classic retro look. The Cortez Basic Leather features a white leather upper with visible stitching and a low-cut collar that provides for flexible movement. The low top also features a lightweight EVA wedge midsole for responsive cushioning subtle herringbone patterns on the outsole and black accents on the oversize Swoosh heel and tongue tab.

shoeName: Nike Vapor Street Off-White Polarized Blue (W)
description: The OFF-WHITE x women’s Vapor Street ‘Polarized Blue’ combines Nike’s performance running heritage with a vibrant color scheme and fashion-forward details from the mind of Virgil Abloh. Built for speed with a lightweight nylon upper in blue and pink the sneaker sits atop a bulky midsole that’s reinforced underfoot by track spikes. Unique details include secondary lacing and Virgil’s signature zip tie.

shoeName: Nike Waffle Racer Off-White Black (W)
description: Part of a three-shoe pack the OFF-WHITE x Wmns Waffle Racer 'Fuchsia' features input from Virgil Abloh. The bold design includes a translucent textile overlay throughout its upper with the black and white finished accented by fuchsia Flywire cables. The medial side sports the usual overbranding while underfoot an exaggerated spiked outsole provides traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Zoom Alphafly Next% Black Electric Green
description: Based on the prototype shoe worn by Eliud Kipchoge when he unofficially broke the two-hour marathon barrier in October 2019 the Air Zoom Alphafly Next% 'Lime Blast' is a performane runner. Built with the lighter more breathable AtomKnit the shoe's upper is supported underfoot by a ZoomX midsole with Zoom Air in the forefoot. A carbon fiber plate provides stability.

shoeName: Nike Epic React Flyknit 2 Hydrogen Blue Sapphire Hyper Pink
Colorway: Hydrogen Blue/Hydrogen Blue-Sapphire-Lime Blast-Hyper Pink-Blue Tint
description: The Epic React Flyknit 2 '8-Bit' looks to 90s technology for inspiration releasing alongside a black 'Pixel' colorway. The shoe's Flyknit upper appears in white supported by a TPU eyestay and blue heel counter. A tonal Swoosh is worked into the side wall while underfoot a white React midsole is accented by Lime Blast and Hyper Pink. The outsole includes rubber inserts at the toe and heel.

shoeName: Nike Vapor Street Off-White Black Laser Fuchsia (W)
description: Dropping in November 2019 as part of Virgil Abloh’s ‘Athlete in Progress’ collection the OFF-WHITE x women’s Vapor Street ‘Laser Fuchsia’ gives the nod to Nike’s track and field heritage. The stylized running shoe features a translucent overlay atop a black nylon upper accented with Laser Fuchsia detailing and Virgil’s signature touches including a plastic zip tie and printed text on the medial sidewall.

shoeName: Nike Waffle Trainer 2 White Black
description: Taking cues from the 1974 original silhouette with an essential two-tone pallete is the Nike Waffle Trainer 2 'White Black.' The upper pairs a white nylon base with off-white suede overlays at the forefoot and heel. Black accents are seen on the leather Swoosh and heel tab stamped with a Nike wordmark in simple white block lettering with additional Nike branding decorating the woven tag looped over the exposed foam tongue. The crisp white foam midsole is supported by a black waffle-traction rubber outsole.

shoeName: Nike Shox Ride 2 SP Supreme White
description: While Supreme is known most for skateboarding they have worked on different silhouettes from the Nike Sportswear catalog in the past including running. Bringing back a mid-2000s Shox style the New York brand makes a bold statement with the Nike Shox Ride 2. This colorway sees a mainly white base offered up in a mesh and leather combo on the upper with grey overlays. Hits of red offer a pop of color including the 'S' Shox logo on the tongue and Swoosh logos on the forefoot and heel. Four Shox columns appear in bright red with 'Supreme' wordmarks in a contrasting white shade. A visible Nike Air unit in the forefoot finishes the look.

shoeName: Nike Air Kukini Spiridon Cage 2 Stussy White
description: Nike teamed up with the Southern California streetwear brand to create the Stussy x Air Zoom Spiridon KK 'Habanero Red.' Inspired by the Air Kukini the shoe's slip-on upper is built with a white mesh base overlaid by tonal web-like detailing. Black branding including the Stussy branding on the tongue contrasts the look while the inner lining adds Habanero Red to the design. Underfoot Phylite and caged Zoom Air combine to provide cushioning.

shoeName: Nike React Element 87 Anthracite Black
description: The Nike React Element 87 'Anthracite' is designed with walking in mind particularly in urban environments. Marked by a contrasting colorway of pure black and white the sneaker features a semi-translucent top made of transparent TPE yarn fabric with a low-ride Swoosh that merges with the midsole and is surrounded by a wavy trail-running lace scheme made of leather suede and reflective detail. Its wide drilled midsole reaction sports translucent black plugs that remain for traction underfoot.
